question:
Let
\[f(x) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
2x & \text{if $0 \le x < 2$}, \\
8 - 2x & \text{if $2 \le x \le 4$}.
\end{array}
\right.\]Find the maximum value of the function.

groundtruth:
We have that
\begin{align*}
\frac{x + y}{z} + \frac{y + z}{x} + \frac{x + z}{y} &= \frac{6 - z}{z} + \frac{6 - x}{x} + \frac{6 - y}{y} \\
&= 6 \left( \frac{1}{x} + \frac{1}{y} + \frac{1}{z} \right) - 3 \\
&= 6 \cdot 2 - 3 = \boxed{9}.
\end{align*}

